This paper deals with detecting and segmenting manipulated images and videos, which is a common problem in computer vision and multimedia analysis. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also uses deep learning techniques, which are commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper deals with image and video forensics, which is a subfield of multimedia analysis (cs.MM) and computer security (cs.CR).
